==English==
===Etymology===
{{G.}} from General Henry Shrapnel, who invented an exploding fragmentation shell.

===Noun===
'''shrapnel'''
# A collective term for [[fragment]]s and [[debris]] thrown out by an [[exploding]] [[shell]] or [[landmine]].
# (slang) Money, especially [[coinage]].
====Translations====
*Finnish: [[sirpale]]
*Portuguese: [[estilhaço]]
*Spanish: [[metralla]]
